## Why This Is Asked

To assess practical cross-tenant crypto governance, KMS design, and audit controls in Azure for enterprise buyers like Oracle, MongoDB, Hugging Face.

## Key Concepts

- Per-tenant KEKs in Azure Key Vault
- Envelope encryption with DEKs
- RBAC and data masking
- Auditing and rollback planning

## Code Example

```javascript
// Pseudo: fetch tenant DEK from Key Vault and wrap data
const { DefaultAzureCredential } = require('@azure/identity');
const { KeyClient, CryptographyClient } = require('@azure/keyvault-keys');

const credential = new DefaultAzureCredential();
const keyClient = new KeyClient(`https://${vaultName}.vault.azure.net`, credential);
const key = await keyClient.getKey(tenantDekName);
const cryptoClient = new CryptographyClient(key.id, credential);
const wrapped = await cryptoClient.wrapKey('RSA-OAEP', dek);
```

## Follow-up Questions

- How would you rotate tenant DEKs without downtime?
- How do you validate data masking in multi-tenant queries?

## Why This Is Asked
Demonstrates ability to implement scalable, workload-driven security without NSG churn, leveraging Azure Firewall Manager, policy-based groups, Private Endpoints, and identity-based controls.

## Key Concepts
- Workload tagging and policy-based groups for dynamic segmentation
- Centralized firewall policies vs. per-VM NSGs
- Private Endpoints for service-to-service traffic
- Managed Identities for authenticating inter-service calls
- Azure Policy to enforce tagging across subscriptions
- Observability via Defender for Cloud and Log Analytics

## Code Example
```javascript
// Example: Azure Policy snippet to require workload-id tag on resources
{
  "policyRule": {
    "if": {
      "allOf": [
        { "field": "type", "in": [
          "Microsoft.Network/virtualNetworks",
          "Microsoft.Network/virtualNetworks/subnets"
        ]},
        { "field": "tags['workload-id']", "exists": "false" }
      ]
    },
    "then": { "effect": "deny" }
  },
  "name": "require-workload-id-tag",
  "properties": {
    "displayName": "Require workload-id tag on network scope",
    "policyType": "BuiltIn"
  }
}
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you test rollback and drift if a workload-id tag is accidentally removed?
- What metrics would you surface to confirm zero-trust posture without degrading performance?
